def convert(val):
  if val == 'yes':
    return 1
  else:
    return 0
    return 'male'
data['smoker'] = data['smoker'].apply(lambda x: convert(x))

def get_income_category(income):
  if income< 200000:
    return "Low"
  elif income <450000:
    return "Medium"
  else:
    return "High"
data['Income_Category'] = data['Total_Income'].apply(lambda x: get_income_category(x))
In [ ]:
def get_height_category(height):
  if height< 160:
    return "Low"
  elif height <185:
    return "Medium"
  else:
    return "High"
data['Height_Category'] = data['Height_in_cm'].apply(lambda x: get_height_category(x))
